 Barberton Primary stood out in their bright red, yellow and blue, at Hoërskool Rob Ferreira and received 12 medals in total, six gold, one silver and five bronze. Scarlett Msthini received two gold medals for the girls’ u/7 60m race, running a time of 10.32s, and for the 80m race, running a quick time of 13.41s. Nothile Nhlengethwa won the u/12 long jump with a distance of 4.01m. Kayla Zwane was the athlete who helped Barberton Primary make their mark as she won four of the nine medals. She won the u/10 high jump with a height of 1.2m and got gold in the 100m running a time of 14.81s. She received a silver medal for running the 80m in 11.93s and received a bronze medal for jumping 3.52m in long jump. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram